\sum_{r=0}^n {{n}\choose{r}} \sin(\alpha +r\beta)
\sum_{r=0}^n {{n}\choose{r}} \sin(\alpha +r\beta)=\text{Imag}[\sum_{r=0}^n\binom nr e^{i(\alpha+r\beta)}]
\sum_{r=0}^n\binom nr e^{i(\alpha+r\beta)}=e^{i\alpha}\sum_{r=0}^n\binom nr (e^{i\beta})^r=e^{i\alpha}(1+e^{i\beta})^n=e^{i\left(\alpha+\frac{\beta}2\right)}\left(e^{i\frac{\beta}2}+e^{-i\frac{\beta}2}\right)^n
\displaystyle e^{ix}=\cos x+i\sin x,e^{-ix}=\cos(-x)+i\sin(-x)=\cos x-i\sin x
\displaystyle\implies e^{ix}+e^{-ix}=\cdots  
